Rank, demean, rescale ESG scores¶

In [140]:
## let's rank them
df = returns.groupby(['fiscal_year', 'month', 'ticker']).mean().total_esg_score.to_frame(name='total_esg')
In [141]:
df.reset_index(inplace=True)  
df['Rank'] = df.groupby(['fiscal_year', 'month'])['total_esg'].rank(ascending=False)

In [143]:
## mean per year-month
df1 = df.groupby(['fiscal_year', 'month']).mean().Rank.to_frame(name='mean_rank')
df1.reset_index(inplace=True)
In [144]:
## min per year-month
df2 = df.groupby(['fiscal_year', 'month']).min().Rank.to_frame(name='min_rank')
df2.reset_index(inplace=True)
In [145]:
## max per year-month
df3 = df.groupby(['fiscal_year', 'month']).max().Rank.to_frame(name='max_rank')
df3.reset_index(inplace=True)
In [146]:
## merge
df = pd.merge(df, df1, on=['fiscal_year', 'month'])
df = pd.merge(df, df2, on=['fiscal_year', 'month'])
df = pd.merge(df, df3, on=['fiscal_year', 'month'])
In [147]:
##demean

df['demeaned_rank'] = df['Rank'] - df['mean_rank']
In [148]:
df['final_esg']= (df['demeaned_rank'] - df['min_rank'])/(df['max_rank']-df['min_rank'])
In [149]:
del df['Rank']

del df['min_rank']
del df['max_rank']
del df['demeaned_rank']
del df['total_esg']

def calcSMB(df):
    """
    Returns SMB for FF
    """
    #Define Quantile
    SQuantile = 0.3
    LQuantile = 0.7
    df["SMB"] = ""
    
    #Assigns stock size based on market cap
    df.SMB[df.MKTCAP <= df.MKTCAP.quantile(SQuantile)] = "SCap"
    df.SMB[(df.MKTCAP > df.MKTCAP.quantile(SQuantile)) & (df.MKTCAP < df.MKTCAP.quantile(LQuantile))] = "MCap"
    df.SMB[df.MKTCAP >= df.MKTCAP.quantile(LQuantile)] = "LCap"
    
    #Calculates average return of stocks in portfolio subset based on size
    SmallCapReturn = df['Monthly total return'].loc[df["SMB"] == "SCap"].mean()
    LargeCapReturn = df['Monthly total return'].loc[df["SMB"] == "LCap"].mean()
    
    #Returns SMB based on definition
    SMB = SmallCapReturn - LargeCapReturn
    return round(SMB, 4)
In [195]:
def calcHML (df):
    """
    Returns HML for FF
    Uses inverse of P/B as proxy for Book/Mkt
    """
    #Define Quantile
    SQuantile = 0.3
    LQuantile = 0.7
    df["HML"] = ""
    
    #Assigns stock size based on market cap
    df.HML[df.book_to_market <= df.book_to_market.quantile(SQuantile)] = "SValue"
    df.HML[(df.book_to_market > df.book_to_market.quantile(SQuantile)) & (df.book_to_market < df.book_to_market.quantile(LQuantile))] = "MValue"
    df.HML[df.book_to_market >= df.book_to_market.quantile(LQuantile)] = "LValue"
    
    #Calculates average return of stocks in portfolio subset based on size
    SmallValueReturn = df['Monthly total return'].loc[df["HML"] == "SValue"].mean()
    LargeValueReturn = df['Monthly total return'].loc[df["HML"] == "LValue"].mean()
    
    #Returns SMB based on definition
    HML = SmallValueReturn - LargeValueReturn
    return round(HML, 4)

        FFA.loc[FFAIndex] = [i, j,

                        calcHML(temp)
